=> SQLite + Entity Framework =
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design
c quoi entity frqmework

Dans Sample c'est quoi reference ?

c quoi dans appsetting.json=
"ConnectionStrings": {
    "DefaultConnection": "Data Source=labtrack.db"
  },



c'est quoi tout ca =

using LabTrack.Api.Data;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

builder.Services.AddControllers();
builder.Services.AddEndpointsApiExplorer();
builder.Services.AddSwaggerGen();

builder.Services.AddDbContext<AppDbContext>(options =>
    options.UseSqlite(builder.Configuration.GetConnectionString("DefaultConnection")));

var app = builder.Build();

if (app.Environment.IsDevelopment())
{
    app.UseSwagger();
    app.UseSwaggerUI();
}

app.UseHttpsRedirection();

app.UseAuthorization();

app.MapControllers();

app.Run();







Installer l'outil de migration :
dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef

pour verrifier :
dotnet ef

Puis :
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
 => analyser les Models (Sample, etc.)
 => creer un dossier Migrations/
 => générer les scripts SQL
dotnet ef database update
 => creer le fichier SQLite (labtrack.db)
 => creer les tables

a chqaue chqngement de models :
dotnet ef migrations add NomDuChangement
dotnet ef database update









